1. install Go (http://golang.org/doc/install.html) 
2. download "router" (http://code.google.com/p/go-router/ or http://channel.sourceforge.net)
3. cd top directory of "router1" or "router2"; make
4. cd "samples" dir, build and run samples: test1, pingpong, chat, dummyserver:
   . build samples against "router1": make
   . build samples against "router2": make VERSION=router2

5. Go website: http://golang.org
6. "router" website: http://code.google.com/p/go-router/
